  "body": "Currently developers can set only one rending mode globally in react-art, using `setCurrent()` of `art/modes/current` module. I would like to provide a way to set own rendering mode per instance of `<Surface>` Component by new property `mode`. \r\n\r\nThis commit enables react-art to provide the followings.\r\n * To set rendering mode of `<Surface>` like `<Surface mode='svg'>` or `<Surface mode='canvas'>`\r\n   If `mode` property is omitted or not available value, canvas is used as default mode.\r\n\r\n * To use multiple `<Surface>` with each other mode at the same time in same document\r\n\r\n * To set mode of Path utility like `Path(path, 'svg')` or `Path(path, 'canvas')`.\r\n   If Path() or Path(path) are used without mode, canvas is used as default mode.\r\n   Path which react-art exports is just utility, not Component(e.g. Shape, Group) which\r\n   can be handled selectively by mode in `createInstance` of `ReactARTHostConfig`.\r\n   Thus this commit provides a way that users of react-art set mode of Path.\r\n\r\nSome test cases are added for validating this commit, and\r\nthe following mock-up functions of DOM are also added to Jest environment for test.\r\n * window.SVGElement.prototype.getBBox\r\n * window.HTMLCanvasElement.prototype.getContext\r\n\r\nThe fixture regarding react-art is also updated to show this commit work well.",
